{"source_key":"sha256-71d3ad43dcb494f5c90ef9dda6b8efdc","record_index":16,"record_hash":"sha256:19a0d086b6f69c0f95fa5ea4a7c10a95fbba1ddb06f1515d675c8a16c581aaaa","timestamp":"2026-05-12T08:44:00.498Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: e934ec\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1783\nOutput:\n     1\t# GitMeta Data Model\n     2\t\n     3\t## Principles\n     4\t\n     5\t- Store durable agent sessions on the `project` target.\n     6\t- Use shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys for GitButler agentlog data.\n     7\t- Do not use `meta:local:*` for main session records.\n     8\t- Redact copied transcript strings before writing.\n     9\t- Keep branch, pull request, change, and commit links as references to durable\n    10\t  project sessions, not owners of transcript data.\n    11\t- Do not write standard `agent:*` keys until there is an interoperability or\n    12\t  publication contract.\n    13\t- Capture does not call GitMeta serialize, push, fetch, or sync. Hook capture\n    14\t  schedules the existing sync command in the background after successful\n    15\t  capture.\n    16\t- Do not persist capture-run buckets. Each invocation merges transcript records\n    17\t  into the same durable session data.\n    18\t\n    19\t## Storage Shape\n    20\t\n    21\tSession index:\n    22\t\n    23\t```text\n    24\tgitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n    25\t```\n    26\t\n    27\tDurable session prefix:\n    28\t\n    29\t```text\n    30\tgitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*\n    31\t```\n    32\t\n    33\tSession-level keys:\n    34\t\n    35\t```text\n    36\tgitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:schema = gitbutler.agent-session.v1\n    37\tgitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:updated-at = <session update timestamp>\n    38\tgitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:sources = set<source-key>\n    39\tgitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:record-hashes = set<sha256:record>\n    40\tgitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:transcript = list<TranscriptRecord JSON>\n    41\t```\n    42\t\n    43\tSource-level keys:\n    44\t\n    45\t```text\n    46\tgitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:agent\n    47\tgitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:provider\n    48\tgitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:model\n    49\tgitbutler:agent-ses\n[TRUNCATED]\nids from\n   120\ttop-level record fields.\n   121\t\n   122\tRecord hashes and dedupe use the original trimmed JSONL bytes, not the redacted\n   123\ttranscript record.\n   124\t\n   125\tStored GitMeta list order is not the public transcript ordering contract.\n   126\tConsumers that render a timeline should sort by transcript fields. Within one\n   127\tsource, sort by `source_key` and `record_index`; across multiple sources, use\n   128\t`timestamp`, `source_key`, `record_index`, and `record_hash` as stable tie\n   129\tbreakers.\n   130\t\n   131\t## Deduplication\n   132\t\n   133\tUse stable record hashes:\n   134\t\n   135\t```text\n   136\tsha256(trimmed raw JSONL line bytes)\n   137\t```\n   138\t\n   139\tCapture checks `:record-hashes` before appending transcript records. The\n   140\ttranscript list remains the append-friendly storage value; the hash set is the\n   141\tcompact dedupe index. Re-running capture against the same transcript is a no-op\n   142\tunless the transcript grew.\n   143\t\n   144\t## Association Model\n   145\t\n   146\tDo not attach transcript data directly to branches, commits, changes, or pull\n   147\trequests in the POC. The project session is the durable object.\n   148\t\n   149\tWhen capture is given an explicit association target, write only this\n   150\trelationship reference:\n   151\t\n   152\t```text\n   153\t<branch/change/commit target>\n   154\t  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n   155\t```\n   156\t\n   157\tSee [Future Use Cases](future-use-cases.md) for access patterns and product\n   158\tmotivation, and [Session Association Risks](session-association-risks.md) for\n   159\twhy inferred relationships should stay cautious.\n   160\t\n   161\t## Publication\n   162\t\n   163\tThe POC writes shareable-ready keys. `but agentlog sync` is the exchange step\n   164\tand uses GitMeta's configured metadata remote behavior. Hook capture starts that\n   165\tsame command in the background after a successful capture. Sync is not scoped to\n   166\tthe `gitbutler:*` agentlog keys, so it may exchange other shareable GitMeta\n   167\tmetadata too.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-12T08:44:00.498Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}